<Layout
  title="About the Institute"
  description="Idara Ulum-Al-Qur'an was established in 1984 at Aligarh Muslim University by alumni of Madrasah al-Islah, following the scholarly methodology of Imam Hamid al-Din Farahi."
  canonicalUrl="/en/about/"
>
  <main class="container page-content">

    <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/en/">Home</a>
      <span>›</span>
      <span>About</span>
    </nav>

    <h1>About the Institute</h1>

    <!-- Tab Nav -->
    <div class="tab-nav">
      <a href="#history" class="tab-link active">History & Mission</a>
      <a href="#aims" class="tab-link">Aims & Objectives</a>
      <a href="#organisation" class="tab-link">Organisation</a>
      <a href="#founding" class="tab-link">Founding Members</a>
      <a href="#committee" class="tab-link">Executive Committee</a>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 1: History -->
    <section id="history" class="content-section">
      <h2>History & Mission</h2>

      <p>
        Idarah Ulum al-Qur'an was established in 1984 by some alumni of
        <strong>Madrasah al-Islah</strong> — a noted seat of Islamic learning in India —
        based at Aligarh Muslim University, Aligarh, and some other academic centres
        within and outside the country. The institute aims at promoting research in
        Qur'anic Studies, working for the dissemination of the teachings of the Noble
        Qur'an, and trying to find solutions for the problems facing the Muslim society
        in particular and humanity at large, in the light of the guidance provided by it.
      </p>

      <p>
        Madrasah al-Islah lays special emphasis on the study and teaching of the Noble
        Qur'an, which is given central place in its curricula. The methodology employed
        for the explanation of the Holy Qur'an and exploring its meanings and subtleties
        is somewhat different from those generally used by scholars working in the area
        of tafsir and Qur'anic studies elsewhere.
      </p>

      <div class="highlight-box">
        <h3>The Farahi Methodology</h3>
        <p>
          This methodology was developed by the renowned twentieth-century scholar,
          exegete, and reformer, <strong>Hamid al-Din Farahi (1863–1930)</strong>,
          who was a great exponent of the concept of coherence (<em>nazm</em>) in the
          Qur'an. After completing his education in the traditional Islamic sciences,
          he joined Mohammedan Anglo-Oriental (M.A.O.) College, Aligarh, in 1891,
          passing his B.A. in 1895. He later served M.A.O. College, Muir College
          Allahabad University, and Dar al-Ulum Hyderabad before devoting the
          remaining years of his life entirely to Qur'anic study.
        </p>
        <p>
          During the last ten years of his life, he tirelessly worked to give concrete
          shape to his Qur'anic thought and implement it at Madrasah al-Islah, which
          was established in 1908. He wrote extensively in Arabic; his disciple and
          intellectual heir, <strong>Amin Ahsan Islahi</strong>, rendered some of his
          more important works into Urdu.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p>
        At Idarah Ulum al-Qur'an, we believe this methodology is best suited for
        pondering over the Holy Qur'an and best calculated to lead to the correct
        understanding of its meanings, subtleties, intricacies, and implications.
        While we strive to propagate this methodology, we are not confined within its
        boundaries. We consider the vast literature produced by successive generations
        of <em>Mufassirun</em> as the most valued treasures of our religious and
        intellectual heritage. There is no place for sectarianism or fanaticism of
        any kind in this organisation.
      </p>

      <p>
        The Noble Qur'an is the last book of guidance for humanity. It was due to the
        realisation of this importance that the Institute of Qur'anic Sciences was
        established in 1984 — to continuously bring its teachings to ever larger
        numbers of people, because the salvation of humanity lies in following the
        precepts and principles enshrined in the Noble Qur'an.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 2: Aims -->
    <section id="aims" class="content-section">
      <h2>Aims & Objectives</h2>

      <p>The Institute was established in 1984 with the following aims and objectives:</p>

      <ul class="aims-list">
        <li>To try to find solutions for the problems confronting the Ummah and humanity at large in the light of the teachings of the Qur'an.</li>
        <li>To try to revive and revitalise the Islamic religious sciences and purify and Islamize the modern sciences in the light of the teachings of the Qur'an.</li>
        <li>To conduct researches on important issues and themes connected with the Qur'an.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Sphere of Work</h3>
      <p>For the purposes of realising these aims and objectives, the Institute has outlined the following programme:</p>

      <ul class="aims-list">
        <li>To publish a standard specialist journal of Qur'anic Studies for the dissemination of Qur'anic sciences and teachings and promoting research in the area.</li>
        <li>To prepare books on issues and themes related to the Qur'an and its worldview and publish them.</li>
        <li>To establish a reference library with special emphasis on Qur'anic studies.</li>
        <li>To arrange for the training and supervision of students to conduct research in the area of Qur'anic Studies and to provide necessary stipends and scholarships.</li>
        <li>To organise discussions and symposia on Qur'anic themes.</li>
        <li>To establish contacts with other centres of Islamic sciences and institutions working for the realisation of the same objectives.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 3: Organisation -->
    <section id="organisation" class="content-section">
      <h2>Organisation of the Institute</h2>

      <div class="org-grid">
        {organisation.map((member) => (
          <div class="org-card">
            <div class="org-role">{member.role}</div>
            <div class="org-name">{member.name}</div>
            <div class="org-detail">{member.detail}</div>
            {member.email && (
              <a href={`mailto:${member.email}`} class="org-email">{member.email}</a>
            )}
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 4: Founding Members -->
    <section id="founding" class="content-section">
      <h2>Founding Members of the Institute</h2>
      <ol class="member-list">
        {foundingMembers.map((name) => (
          <li>{name}</li>
        ))}
      </ol>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 5: Executive Committee -->
    <section id="committee" class="content-section">
      <h2>Members of the Present Executive Committee</h2>
      <ol class="member-list">
        {executiveCommittee.map((name) => (
          <li>{name}</li>
        ))}
      </ol>
    </section>

  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
.page-content {
  padding-top: 2.5rem;
  padding-bottom: 4rem;
}

.breadcrumb {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.5rem;
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  color: var(--color-muted);
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.breadcrumb a {
  color: var(--color-link);
}

h1 {
  font-size: 2.25rem;
  color: var(--color-primary);
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  padding-bottom: 1rem;
  border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);
}

/* ─── Tab Nav ─── */
.tab-nav {
  display: flex;
  gap: 0;
  border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);
  margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.tab-link {
  padding: 0.65rem 1.1rem;
  font-size: 0.88rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--color-muted);
  border-bottom: 3px solid transparent;
  margin-bottom: -2px;
  transition: color 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;
}

.tab-link:hover {
  color: var(--color-primary);
  text-decoration: none;
  border-bottom-color: var(--color-border);
}

.tab-link.active {
  color: var(--color-primary);
  border-bottom-color: var(--color-primary);
}

/* ─── Content Sections ─── */
.content-section {
  margin-bottom: 4rem;
  padding-bottom: 3rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
}

.content-section:last-child {
  border-bottom: none;
}

h2 {
  font-size: 1.5rem;
  color: var(--color-primary);
  margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
}

h3 {
  font-size: 1.15rem;
  color: var(--color-primary);
  margin-top: 1.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}

p {
  font-size: 1rem;
  line-height: 1.85;
  color: var(--color-text);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  max-width: 780px;
}

strong {
  color: var(--color-primary);
}

em {
  color: var(--color-primary);
  font-style: italic;
}

/* ─── Highlight Box ─── */
.highlight-box {
  background: var(--color-white);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
  border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
  padding: 1.5rem;
  margin: 1.5rem 0;
}

.highlight-box h3 {
  margin-top: 0;
  color: var(--color-primary);
}

.highlight-box p {
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}

.highlight-box p:last-child {
  margin-bottom: 0;
}

/* ─── Aims List ─── */
.aims-list {
  padding-left: 1.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  max-width: 780px;
}

.aims-list li {
  font-size: 1rem;
  line-height: 1.85;
  color: var(--color-text);
  margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
}

/* ─── Organisation Grid ─── */
.org-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
  gap: 1rem;
}

.org-card {
  background: var(--color-white);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 1.25rem;
}

.org-role {
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.07em;
  color: var(--color-accent);
  font-weight: 700;
  margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
}

.org-name {
  font-size: 1rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--color-primary);
  margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
}

.org-detail {
  font-size: 0.87rem;
  color: var(--color-muted);
  line-height: 1.6;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.org-email {
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  color: var(--color-link);
}

.org-email:hover {
  text-decoration: underline;
}

/* ─── Member Lists ─── */
.member-list {
  column-count: 2;
  column-gap: 2rem;
  padding-left: 1.5rem;
  max-width: 780px;
}

.member-list li {
  font-size: 0.97rem;
  line-height: 1.75;
  color: var(--color-text);
  margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  break-inside: avoid;
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  h1 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
  }

  .tab-link {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.7rem;
  }

  .org-grid {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }

  .member-list {
    column-count: 1;
  }
}
</style>